    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="988"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d988">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.3212/9a.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Before receiving your telegram, arrangements had been made with Brazil for
                    Brazilian Legation at Mexico City to take over records, archives and property of
                    the American Embassy. You will act accordingly. Wherever there is a Brazilian
                    Consul, our Consulate will be turned over to him upon the withdrawal of the
                    American Consul. We are arranging to have the Consul of France take charge where
                    there is no Brazilian Consul. Notice will be sent to consulates direct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
